        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          Another good performance and result by Leicester. If we were to end the season today, both Vardy and Mahrez would be genuine player of the year candidates. Credit has to go to Ranieri. Both the aforementioned looked "ok" last season but he has gotten the best out of them. The only thing I think Ranieri didn't do correctly tonight was bring Inler on for Ulloa to make it a midfield 3 after the Mahrez goal. Other than that, excellent. For Chelsea, they obviously have too many fair-weather players (Hazard, Fabregas and Oscar being the 3 worst), they need to drop Costa and put Remy in the 9. He showed more coming on for 15 minutes than Costa has all season. Matic played alright, although Leicester are hardly the 'dominate in midfield' type. Ramires didn't do a thing, as per, and the defence looks likely concede at any time. Mourinho teams are based on defensive stability and that clearly isn't there. Not sure why Rahman has been dropped when Ivanovic has been retained. Ah well.
